## 🎯 Overview

**Thuva Waves** is a modern, scalable ride-booking platform built on the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js). It supports three distinct user roles — Passenger, Driver, and Admin — with real-time ride matching, live GPS tracking, secure payments, and a full admin analytics dashboard.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React.js, Vite, React Router, Axios, Tailwind CSS |
| **Backend** | Node.js, Express.js |
| **Database** | MongoDB with Mongoose ODM |
| **Authentication** | JWT (JSON Web Tokens) |
| **Maps & Geolocation** | Google Maps API |
| **Real-time Communication** | Socket.io |
| **File Upload / Storage** | Cloudinary |
| **Push Notifications** | Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) |
| **Password Security** | bcrypt |

---

## 👥 User Roles

1. **Passenger** — books rides, tracks drivers, pays, and reviews
2. **Driver** — accepts rides, navigates, and earns
3. **Admin** — manages the entire platform

---

## ✨ Features

### 🧍 Passenger
- Register / Login with JWT authentication
- Edit profile
- Book rides with pickup & drop-off location selection
- Real-time fare estimation
- Live driver tracking on map
- Ride history
- Cancel ride
- Rate and review drivers
- View payment history

### 🚘 Driver
- Register / Login
- Upload driving license & vehicle details (Cloudinary)
- Toggle online/offline availability status
- Accept or reject incoming ride requests
- Turn-by-turn navigation route (Google Maps)
- Earnings dashboard
- Ride history
- View passenger ratings

### 🛡️ Admin
- Dashboard analytics (rides, users, revenue trends)
- Manage users (view, block/unblock)
- Manage drivers
- Approve or reject driver registrations
- Manage all rides
- Revenue analytics
- Block/unblock accounts

---

## 🔄 Ride Flow

```
1. Passenger requests a ride (pickup + drop location)
        ↓
2. Nearby available drivers notified in real-time (Socket.io)
        ↓
3. Driver accepts the ride request
        ↓
4. Passenger sees live driver location on map
        ↓
5. Driver arrives & starts the ride
        ↓
6. Ride completes at destination
        ↓
7. Payment is recorded
        ↓
8. Passenger submits rating & review
```

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema (Collections)

| Collection | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Users** | Passenger account details |
| **Drivers** | Driver profile, license, approval status |
| **Vehicles** | Vehicle info linked to a driver |
| **Rides** | Ride requests, status, route, fare |
| **Payments** | Transaction records per ride |
| **Reviews** | Ratings & feedback between passengers/drivers |
| **Notifications** | FCM push notification logs |

---

## 🔌 API Endpoints

### Authentication
```
POST   /api/auth/register
POST   /api/auth/login
POST   /api/auth/refresh-token
```

### Users
```
GET    /api/users/profile
PUT    /api/users/profile
GET    /api/users/ride-history
```

### Drivers
```
POST   /api/drivers/register
PUT    /api/drivers/status          # online/offline
POST   /api/drivers/vehicle
GET    /api/drivers/earnings
```

### Rides
```
POST   /api/rides/request
PUT    /api/rides/:id/accept
PUT    /api/rides/:id/reject
PUT    /api/rides/:id/start
PUT    /api/rides/:id/complete
PUT    /api/rides/:id/cancel
GET    /api/rides/:id/track
```

### Payments
```
POST   /api/payments/process
GET    /api/payments/history
```

### Reviews
```
POST   /api/reviews
GET    /api/reviews/:userId
```

### Admin
```
GET    /api/admin/dashboard
GET    /api/admin/users
PUT    /api/admin/users/:id/block
GET    /api/admin/drivers/pending
PUT    /api/admin/drivers/:id/approve
GET    /api/admin/revenue
```

